---
import ProLayout from '../../../layouts/ProLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<ProLayout
  title="Governance · Pro · America's School Trust Library"
  description="Institutional governance records for America's School Trust Library now live at schooltrusts.org; this route remains as a stable pointer."
  sourceId="pro-governance"
  pageLabel="Governance"
>
  <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:underline">
    <p class="kicker">Institutional Records</p>
    <h1>Governance Records</h1>

    <p>
      America's School Trust Library is now organizing as a nonprofit public
      benefit corporation under Oregon law. The institutional record lives at
      <a href="https://schooltrusts.org" rel="noopener">schooltrusts.org</a>,
      where prospective directors, collaborators, and readers can see the
      current public-facing formation materials.
    </p>

    <section class="pointer-grid" aria-label="Institutional governance links">
      <a href="https://schooltrusts.org/about" rel="noopener">
        <span>Institution</span>
        <strong>About the Library</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="https://schooltrusts.org/bylaws" rel="noopener">
        <span>Draft</span>
        <strong>Bylaws for Consideration</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="https://schooltrusts.org/organizing" rel="noopener">
        <span>Formation</span>
        <strong>Organizing Steps</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="https://schooltrusts.org/help" rel="noopener">
        <span>Participation</span>
        <strong>Ways to Help</strong>
      </a>
    </section>

    <p>
      This .net page remains in place so older citations do not break. The
      Pro pages that still belong inside the record building are the Library's
      operating pages: <a href="/pro/editorial-standards/">Editorial Standards</a>,
      <a href="/pro/collection-development/">Collection Development</a>,
      <a href="/pro/metadata-schema/">Metadata and Provenance Schema</a>, and
      <a href="/pro/dispute-resolution/">Dispute Resolution</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

  <style>
    .kicker {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: #A88A4E;
      margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    }
    .pointer-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(12rem, 1fr));
      gap: 0.75rem;
      margin: 1.4rem 0;
    }
    .pointer-grid a {
      display: block;
      padding: 0.95rem 1rem;
      border: 1px solid #d8d1c2;
      border-radius: 6px;
      background: #fffdf7;
      text-decoration: none !important;
    }
    .pointer-grid span {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: #8a6f2f;
    }
    .pointer-grid strong {
      color: #1e3a5f;
    }
  </style>
</ProLayout>
